Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.95,0:01:34.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.25,0:01:39.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Poison has taken a beautiful girl and\nturned her into a sleeping beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.39,0:01:46.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A letter from a dead man led three men\nback to loathsome memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.60,0:01:53.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear it, the beautiful melody entitled\N"Nightmare" that my friend is playing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.96,0:01:57.93,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 11:\NAn Engagement Broken
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:05.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Papa's here. Now you guys\nare gonna get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.82,0:02:07.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please step aside,\NMadame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.55,0:02:10.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.09,0:02:12.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.10,0:02:25.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NMadame?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.90,0:02:27.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mama! Mama, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.94,0:02:33.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter with me?\NI don't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.68,0:02:40.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Renaud! Get the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.35,0:02:41.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.59,0:02:46.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Heloise?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.26,0:02:48.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Heloise!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.70,0:02:56.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get after them!\NThey've taken my daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.67,0:02:57.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Catch them!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.94,0:03:01.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.74,0:03:02.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here they come!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.18,0:03:09.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!\NAll right, watch this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.62,0:03:14.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Renaud?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.75,0:03:18.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert! Block the road!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.90,0:04:00.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.93,0:04:02.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.83,0:04:05.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky that it wasn't\nanything serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.80,0:04:09.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wish that you wouldn't\nworry me so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.97,0:04:11.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cut that out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.94,0:04:18.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, what you guys did is\nusually referred to as "kidnapping"!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.35,0:04:19.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like you're one to talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.59,0:04:27.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once people know why we did it,\NI'm sure they'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.13,0:04:33.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But it's gonna be Monsieur Villefort\nwho tries the case. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.50,0:04:35.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.92,0:05:02.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The dead man has\ncome back to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.53,0:05:07.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He would never forget what we did,\nnot in a million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.70,0:05:12.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.31,0:05:18.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. Today was a\nterrible day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.55,0:05:25.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you go\nthis morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.05,0:05:27.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The funeral of\nsomeone I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.42,0:05:34.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to hide it from me. A letter\nfrom Edmond came this morning, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.73,0:05:40.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know\nabout that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.26,0:05:42.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what this\nis all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.00,0:05:44.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was just\na tasteless prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.07,0:05:47.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why would anyone use that name\nfor a prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:49.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.71,0:05:53.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond was accused of treason and died\nin the far reaches of space, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:55.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.81,0:05:58.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know\nanything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.25,0:06:02.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Fernand, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.42,0:06:05.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead and gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.22,0:06:08.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're hiding something\nfrom me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.36,0:06:13.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The man is dead!\NI'm not hiding anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.03,0:06:16.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He died in prison!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.53,0:06:19.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You still can't forget what\nhappened 20 years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.97,0:06:26.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?! Have you been thinking about\nthat man every day for the past 20 years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.58,0:06:31.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still in love\nwith him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.88,0:06:35.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was only because I was told\nthat he was dead that l...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.93,0:06:45.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You only did what because\nyou were told he was dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.10,0:06:50.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were told he was dead, so you gave up\non him and married me instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.84,0:06:53.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.14,0:06:55.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.32,0:07:15.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.06,0:07:19.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.54,0:07:26.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mercedes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.41,0:07:31.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The crime lab determined\nthat the cause was a poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.28,0:07:35.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a botanical toxin of some sort. We're\nworking as fast as we can to identify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.71,0:07:36.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.98,0:07:39.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your Honor, I suggest that you\nexercise extreme caution.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.25,0:07:42.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit might still\nbe in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.72,0:07:45.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've already dismissed\nall the servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.42,0:07:47.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to\nworry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:48.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.23,0:07:51.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are two things\nthat you must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.60,0:07:54.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The first is to prevent news of this\nfrom leaking out to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.50,0:07:58.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The second is my daughter.\NFind out where my daughter is without delay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.94,0:08:02.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The search team arrived\nin Marseilles this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.47,0:08:04.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They will probably locate her\nby the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.44,0:08:08.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Notify me when you\nfind her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.28,0:08:10.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,An arrest warrant\nis standing by.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.32,0:08:14.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, just pinpoint\nwhere they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.65,0:08:16.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Leave them at large\nfor the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.15,0:08:18.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.66,0:08:52.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Franz?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.63,0:08:58.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.87,0:09:04.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't expecting you\nto be here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.34,0:09:11.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a reason that you\ndon't want to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.64,0:09:12.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.18,0:09:15.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Want to read\nthis letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.71,0:09:17.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's it from?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.88,0:09:21.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maximilien?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.92,0:09:24.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The guy sure has\nneat handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.42,0:09:26.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, as opposed\nto you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.12,0:09:27.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're pushing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.16,0:09:33.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So I guess he made it\nto Marseilles safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.56,0:09:36.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right about now, I bet he's freaking out\nover what he's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.33,0:09:38.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's very possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.17,0:09:44.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.24,0:09:49.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person is Valentine's current\nmother? What's Madame Heloise like?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.38,0:09:55.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? She's young,\nand beautiful, and intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:09:59.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she is, isn't she?\NThat's what I thought, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:04.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, mind if I\nask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.39,0:10:05.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.93,0:10:10.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You said that you saw Madame Villefort\nand the Count in the greenhouse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.07,0:10:12.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.17,0:10:16.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since you told me about it back at Auteuil,\nit's been nagging at me. That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.14,0:10:18.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:21.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the Count happen to pick her\nto have an affair with?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.88,0:10:25.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have to think he targeted her specifically\nand made his move on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.78,0:10:27.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And anyway, how is it that he could\ntake one look at your symptoms...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.68,0:10:29.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and know right away\nthat it was poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.65,0:10:33.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, are you implying that\nthe Count is the one behind all this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.62,0:10:35.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that,\nnot for a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.26,0:10:39.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for the Count, I might\nnot be standing here today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:45.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Albert. Even if you\nlooked all over Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.94,0:10:48.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...you wouldn't find many people who just\nhappen to have antidotes on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.67,0:10:49.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not even doctors would!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.17,0:10:54.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Were you able to save me, then?\NYou couldn't do a thing to help, am I right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.05,0:10:58.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The only reason I survived was\nbecause the Count was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.12,0:11:04.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What would the Count hope to gain by\ntrying to poison people? Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.96,0:11:08.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.\NBut I can sense it in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:09.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sense what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.89,0:11:13.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A deep darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.44,0:11:20.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I bothered you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.51,0:11:27.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert! Take a good look at him!\NLook at the real Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.95,0:11:31.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.28,0:11:35.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have faith in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.89,0:11:40.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who knows\nthe real Count... is me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.49,0:12:20.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(407,210)\frz20\c&H547268&\4c&H293C26&\2c&H547268&\bord0}Encyclopedia of Toxicology
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.67,0:12:23.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.40,0:12:25.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've come around?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.04,0:12:31.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to me?\NMy memories are a jumble...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:32.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.91,0:12:41.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't seem to shake off\nthis lethargy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.95,0:12:45.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's because of the poison,\ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.69,0:12:46.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.49,0:12:52.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good amount of poison\Ncoursing through your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.33,0:12:58.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get that ring\nfrom the Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:13:01.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about?\NWhat are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.37,0:13:05.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to change my line\nof questioning, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:10.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever\nseen this before?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.01,0:13:13.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... have no idea\nwhat that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.08,0:13:18.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I got it out of your jewelry box.\NDoes that mean that this is perfume?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.06,0:13:22.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea.\NIt isn't mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.79,0:13:27.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying\nto ruin me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.96,0:13:31.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What you've done can never\nbe set to rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.17,0:13:34.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If it gets out that my\nwife is a poisoner,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.41,0:13:38.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...what do you think will happen\nto all that I've built?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.78,0:13:43.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your plans haven't run their\ncourse yet, have they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.28,0:13:49.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who else is there?\NValentine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:53.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me! How many more\ndo you plan to kill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.39,0:13:58.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is my name on your\nlist, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.20,0:14:03.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!\NI had intended to kill you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.50,0:14:08.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I only need my\ndarling Edouard!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.14,0:14:14.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you, acting like some\nhigh and mighty saint!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.48,0:14:16.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won't stand for\nthese insults!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.88,0:14:20.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I dare you to speak to me\nin that tone again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.15,0:14:22.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill myself\nright here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.32,0:14:26.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To the mighty Crown Prosecutor, the man who\nvalues appearances more than anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.89,0:14:28.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...there could be no greater scandal,\ncould there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.61,0:14:45.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You... you don't mean\nto suggest that l...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.21,0:14:49.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NAren't you going to drink it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.82,0:14:53.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of man are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.76,0:15:01.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you only capable of\nkilling other people?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.00,0:15:09.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow morning, you will be\ntransferred to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.60,0:15:12.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've had a private room with barred windows\nprepared for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:17.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The quarters won't be very spacious, but you\nwill spend the rest of your days there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.71,0:15:19.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Along with your poisons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.51,0:15:55.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert! Take a good look at him!\NLook at the real Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.85,0:16:00.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know the real Count\nbetter than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:03.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.72,0:16:07.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Monsieur Albert.\NHow are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.96,0:16:10.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be in rather\nhigh spirits today, Count
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:20.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, I take it that Mademoiselle\NValentine was saved, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.10,0:16:26.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right. She's recuperating in Marseilles now\nwith Maximilien watching over her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.38,0:16:28.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is wonderful news.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.78,0:16:35.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but we got there too late,\nand Valois, their butler, died...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:41.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were able to save the life of your\Ndear friend. You needn't feel sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.33,0:16:45.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And Madame Villefort has\nhad a mental breakdown...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.06,0:16:50.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, why do you think those horrible\nthings happened to the Villeforts?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.97,0:16:55.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.74,0:16:59.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are no coincidences\nin this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.81,0:17:02.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It all comes down\nto karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.21,0:17:04.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean\nby that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.42,0:17:08.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that the Villeforts\Ndeserved what happened to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:12.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and I met\nthat day on Luna.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.99,0:17:17.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you feel that our meeting\nwas a chance encounter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.03,0:17:22.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But in fate, there are\nno coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.83,0:17:27.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just as that setting sun does so\naccording to the laws of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.34,0:17:32.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...fate, too, is composed\nof unyielding necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.88,0:17:35.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such thing as\ncoincidence in your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:38.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. There is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.45,0:17:42.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What I have is the power\nof a strong will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.95,0:17:48.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if other people accept coincidences\nand are tossed about by them, I do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.59,0:17:54.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For you see, I have forged my own destiny\nthrough the power of my own will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.90,0:17:59.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Forge your own destiny\nthrough the power of your will...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.44,0:18:05.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is why we met,\nand that is why we are here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.68,0:18:08.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, I want\nto change.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.68,0:18:10.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be a strong man\nlike you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.85,0:18:15.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, allow me to offer you\nthese words of advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.46,0:18:28.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time.\NAnd hold out hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.80,0:18:35.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time...\NAnd hold out hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.48,0:18:41.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.98,0:18:45.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you sitting there with that\nidiotic expression on your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.35,0:18:48.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie?\NHow's your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.18,0:18:52.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't seem to be anything serious.\NShe's been in a bad mood ever since, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.32,0:18:53.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.36,0:18:55.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But enough about that,\nlisten to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.43,0:18:59.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be playing the piano at the\nconcert hall along with the orchestra!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.03,0:19:01.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At the opera house?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.10,0:19:05.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. My dream is finally coming true.\nI just got the news!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:08.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They've recognized my talent\non the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.58,0:19:13.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.78,0:19:18.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you come\nhear me play, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.88,0:19:19.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.12,0:19:23.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's so amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.02,0:19:26.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I should get back\nand practice some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.22,0:19:27.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Eugenie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.63,0:19:32.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your playing that night\nat Auteuil...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:35.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was... How can I put it?\NIt was really great.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.87,0:19:38.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You could really tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:44.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:18.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Flowers for you, Mademoiselle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.56,0:20:41.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Andrea Cavalcanti?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.78,0:21:02.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.86,0:21:09.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.39,0:21:12.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.90,0:21:23.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Danglars says that he wants to break\Noff your engagement to Eugenie.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.48,0:21:32.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.75,0:23:14.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have to know how she really feels.\NI run to the opera house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.95,0:23:16.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have to know how I really feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:20.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo act 12:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.79,0:23:20.17,count fo,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 12:\NEncore
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:21.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Encore."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.52,0:23:23.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
